    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Start cooking the chorizo</strong></p> <p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong>\u00a0olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat.</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 4-5 minutes or until starting to crisp.</p> <p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the <strong>brown</strong>\u00a0<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>onions</strong></span>.</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong>. Boil a kettle.</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jumbo-king-prawn-chorizo-and-saffron-risotto-grape-and-chicory-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare your\u00a0saffron stock\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Once the chorizo is starting to crisp, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 5-6 minutes further or until the onion has softened.</p> <p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 800ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.6L]</span> <strong>boiled water,\u00a0</strong>add the <strong>saffron</strong>\u00a0and set aside to infuse \u2013 this is your <strong>saffron stock</strong>.</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jumbo-king-prawn-chorizo-and-saffron-risotto-grape-and-chicory-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Begin the risotto</strong>\u00a0</p> <p>Once the onion has softened, add the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Chinese rice\u00a0</strong></span><strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">wine</span> </strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">and</span>\u00a0<strong>arborio rice</strong>\u00a0and cook for 1 minute, stirring to coat the grains in the oil.</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jumbo-king-prawn-chorizo-and-saffron-risotto-grape-and-chicory-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Continue to cook your saffron risotto</strong></p> <p>Add 1/3 of the <strong>saffron\u00a0stock</strong>\u00a0and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until it has absorbed.</p> <p>Continue to add the <strong>stock</strong> a little at a time, stirring continuously for 30-35 minutes or until the stock has been absorbed and the rice is cooked.</p> <p>Tip: add a splash more boiled water if it's looking a little dry or the rice isn't quite cooked!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jumbo-king-prawn-chorizo-and-saffron-risotto-grape-and-chicory-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare the grape &amp; chicory salad</strong></p> <p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>grapes</strong> in half.</p> <p>Separate the\u00a0<strong>chicory leaves </strong>until you're just left with the <strong>core</strong>. Cut the <strong>core</strong> into quarters.</p> <p>Combine the\u00a0<strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>\u00a0and 2 tbsp\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong>\u00a0olive oil\u00a0</strong>in a bowl. Add a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>sugar</strong>\u00a0and mix well until combined \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>balsamic dressing</strong>.</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jumbo-king-prawn-chorizo-and-saffron-risotto-grape-and-chicory-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Finish your saffron risotto</strong></p> <p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks.</p> <p>Chop the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half.</p> <p>Once the rice is cooked, add a large knob of <strong>butter</strong>, most of the<strong> chopped parsley</strong> and the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon </strong>\u2013<strong>\u00a0</strong>this is your<strong> chorizo &amp; saffron risotto</strong>.</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jumbo-king-prawn-chorizo-and-saffron-risotto-grape-and-chicory-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the jumbo king prawns</strong></p> <p>Heat a separate frying pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and drizzle of <strong>olive</strong>\u00a0<strong>oil </strong>over a high heat.</p> <p>Pat the <strong>jumbo king prawns</strong> dry with kitchen roll.</p> <p>Once hot, add the<strong> jumbo king prawns</strong>\u00a0with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 minutes, turning frequently, or until cooked through.\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/jumbo-king-prawn-chorizo-and-saffron-risotto-grape-and-chicory-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve <span class=\"text-highlight\">up!</span></strong></p> <p>Combine the <strong>chicory</strong>, <strong>grapes</strong> and<strong> balsamic dressing</strong> and give everything a good mix up.</p> <p>Serve the <strong>jumbo king prawns</strong> over the<strong>\u00a0chorizo &amp; saffron risotto </strong>and spoon over any juices from the prawn pan.</p> <p>Sprinkle over the<strong> remaining parsley </strong>and garnish with a<strong> lemon wedge</strong>.</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
